<paragraph id="CE4836FFBD14FFE625EAFDD4FDD998BB" blockId="19.[151,555,475,502]" box="[151,555,475,502]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<heading id="95008193BD14FFE625EAFDD4FDD998BB" bold="true" box="[151,555,475,502]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" reason="1">
<emphasis id="FC83EAEDBD14FFE625EAFDD4FDD998BB" bold="true" box="[151,555,475,502]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="09F74D7CBD14FFE62593FDD3FDD998BB" authority="Dallas, 1852" authorityName="Dallas" authorityYear="1852" box="[238,555,475,502]" class="Insecta" family="Rhopalidae" genus="Maccevethus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FC83EAEDBD14FFE62593FDD3FE7E98B8" bold="true" box="[238,396,476,502]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Maccevethus</emphasis>
Dallas, 
<number id="783F24D8BD14FFE6248DFDD4FDD998BB" box="[496,555,475,501]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1852.0">1852</number>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CE4836FFBD14FFE625EAFE2DFDDD9A88" blockId="19.[151,1436,546,966]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis id="FC83EAEDBD14FFE625EAFE2DFCF49B75" bold="true" box="[151,774,546,571]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
General comments on genus 
<taxonomicName id="09F74D7CBD14FFE62777FE2DFCF49B75" authority="Dallas." authorityName="Dallas." box="[522,774,546,571]" class="Insecta" family="Rhopalidae" genus="Maccevethus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FC83EAEDBD14FFE62777FE2DFD559B75" bold="true" box="[522,679,546,571]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Maccevethus</emphasis>
Dallas.
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
The species of this genus are so similar one from the others that only males can be specifically identified. Much confusion reigned in the systematics of this genus (see 
<bibRefCitation id="AA664B0EBD14FFE625AFFE64FE139BCC" author="Kment" box="[210,481,618,642]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refString="Kment, P. &amp; Banar, P. (2010) On the taxonomy and distribution of the genus Maccevethus (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Rhopalidae). Acta Musei Moraviae, Scientiae biologicae (Brno), 95 (1), 15 - 47." type="journal article" year="2010">
Kment &amp; Baňař 
<number id="783F24D8BD14FFE624DCFE65FE139BCC" box="[417,481,618,642]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="AA664B0EBD14FFE62484FE64FCE49BCC" author="Kment" box="[505,790,618,642]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refString="Kment, P. &amp; Banar, P. (2010) On the taxonomy and distribution of the genus Maccevethus (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Rhopalidae). Acta Musei Moraviae, Scientiae biologicae (Brno), 95 (1), 15 - 47." type="journal article" year="2010">
Kment &amp; Baňař (
<number id="783F24D8BD14FFE627ADFE65FCFC9BCC" box="[720,782,618,642]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="2010.0">2010</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
studied the collections of several museum in 
<collectingCountry id="B6E0766FBD14FFE6202EFE65FEF39BE8" name="Czech Republic" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Czech Republic</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="B6E0766FBD14FFE62446FE80FE539BE9" box="[315,417,655,679]" name="Hungary" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Hungary</collectingCountry>
and their carefull examinations led them to consider the following taxa: 
<taxonomicName id="09F74D7CBD14FFE62079FE81FE379B84" authority="Fabricius, 1794" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1794" class="Insecta" family="Rhopalidae" genus="Maccevethus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="errans">
<emphasis id="FC83EAEDBD14FFE62079FE81FF169B85" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Maccevethus errans</emphasis>
(Fabricius, 
<number id="783F24D8BD14FFE62400FEBDFE4E9B84" box="[381,444,690,714]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1794.0">1794</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="09F74D7CBD14FFE624AAFEBBFCAC9B84" authority="Kolenati, 1845" authorityName="Kolenati" authorityYear="1845" box="[471,862,690,715]" class="Insecta" family="Rhopalidae" genus="Maccevethus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasicus">
<emphasis id="FC83EAEDBD14FFE624AAFEBBFD779B85" box="[471,645,692,715]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">M. caucasicus</emphasis>
(Kolenati, 
<number id="783F24D8BD14FFE6266BFEBDFCA69B84" box="[790,852,690,714]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1845.0">1845</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="09F74D7CBD14FFE6260DFEBBFAC09B84" authority="Signoret, 1862" authorityName="Signoret" authorityYear="1862" box="[880,1330,690,715]" class="Insecta" family="Rhopalidae" genus="Maccevethus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="corsicus" subSpecies="corsicus">
<emphasis id="FC83EAEDBD14FFE6260DFEBBFB9D9B85" box="[880,1135,692,715]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">M. corsicus corsicus</emphasis>
Signoret, 
<number id="783F24D8BD14FFE62188FEBDFAC09B84" box="[1269,1330,690,714]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1862.0">1862</number>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="09F74D7CBD14FFE62001FEBBFDEF9BA0" authority="Jakovlev, 1882" authorityName="Jakovlev" authorityYear="1882" class="Insecta" family="Rhopalidae" genus="Maccevethus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="corsicus" subSpecies="persicus">
<emphasis id="FC83EAEDBD14FFE62001FEBBFE909BA0" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">M. corsicus persicus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="AA664B0EBD14FFE62414FED9FDEF9BA0" author="Jakovlev" box="[361,541,726,750]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refString="Jakovlev, V. E. (1882) Contributions to the fauna of bugs of Russia and the neighbouring countries. IX. Bulletin de la Societe Imperiale des Naturalistes Moscou, 56, 345 - 371 [In Russian and German]." type="journal article" year="1882">
Jakovlev, 
<number id="783F24D8BD14FFE624A2FED9FDEF9BA0" box="[479,541,726,750]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1882.0">1882</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Although these authors say that they “must admit that our identifications of 
<taxonomicName id="09F74D7CBD14FFE625EAFEF3FE7B9A5D" box="[151,393,764,787]" class="Insecta" family="Rhopalidae" genus="Maccevethus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="corsicus" subSpecies="persicus">
<emphasis id="FC83EAEDBD14FFE625EAFEF3FE7B9A5D" box="[151,393,764,787]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">M. corsicus persicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are rather arbitrary,” they reinstated 
<taxonomicName id="09F74D7CBD14FFE62646FEF3FC6F9A5D" box="[827,925,764,787]" class="Insecta" family="Rhopalidae" genus="Maccevethus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persicus">
<emphasis id="FC83EAEDBD14FFE62646FEF3FC6F9A5D" box="[827,925,764,787]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">persicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at subspecic rank, a taxon from which they studied only few samples from 
<collectingCountry id="B6E0766FBD14FFE6276FFF11FD539A78" box="[530,673,798,822]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="B6E0766FBD14FFE627A3FF11FCA69A78" box="[734,852,798,822]" name="Mongolia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
. They reported it also, according to other earlier papers, from 
<collectingCountry id="B6E0766FBD14FFE62442FF4CFE809A14" box="[319,370,835,858]" name="Iran" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Iran</collectingCountry>
, Asian 
<collectingCountry id="B6E0766FBD14FFE624ABFF4DFD909A14" box="[470,610,834,858]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="B6E0766FBD14FFE62709FF4DFD199A14" box="[628,747,834,858]" name="Tajikistan" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Tajikistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="B6E0766FBD14FFE62780FF4DFC539A14" box="[765,929,834,858]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="B6E0766FBD14FFE62691FF4DFB869A14" box="[1004,1140,834,858]" name="Uzbekistan" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Uzbekistan</collectingCountry>
. We agree with several authors (including 
<bibRefCitation id="AA664B0EBD14FFE62407FF68FD8D9A30" author="Kment" box="[378,639,870,894]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refString="Kment, P. &amp; Banar, P. (2010) On the taxonomy and distribution of the genus Maccevethus (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Rhopalidae). Acta Musei Moraviae, Scientiae biologicae (Brno), 95 (1), 15 - 47." type="journal article" year="2010">
Kment &amp; Baňař 
<number id="783F24D8BD14FFE6273EFF69FD8D9A30" box="[579,639,870,894]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) that 
<taxonomicName id="09F74D7CBD14FFE627BAFF68FCDB9A30" box="[711,809,871,894]" class="Insecta" family="Rhopalidae" genus="Maccevethus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="corsicus">
<emphasis id="FC83EAEDBD14FFE627BAFF68FCDB9A30" box="[711,809,871,894]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">corsicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="09F74D7CBD14FFE6261BFF68FC359A30" box="[870,967,871,894]" class="Insecta" family="Rhopalidae" genus="Maccevethus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persicus">
<emphasis id="FC83EAEDBD14FFE6261BFF68FC359A30" box="[870,967,871,894]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">persicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are not always clear cut and that their separation is not easy to do above all in intermediates (an opinion by 
<bibRefCitation id="AA664B0EBD14FFE62146FF85FB0D9AEC" author="Moulet" box="[1083,1279,906,930]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refString="Moulet, P. (1994 b) Le genre Maccevethus Dallas, 1852 (Heteroptera, Rhopalidae). Bulletin de la societe entomologique de France, 99, 63 - 67." type="journal article" year="1994" yearSuffix="b">
Moulet [
<number id="783F24D8BD14FFE621DAFF85FB1A9AEC" box="[1191,1256,906,930]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1994.0">1994</number>
b]
</bibRefCitation>
, but greatly misunderstood by 
<bibRefCitation id="AA664B0EBD14FFE62412FFA1FDD09A88" author="Kerzhner" box="[367,546,942,966]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refString="Kerzhner, I. M. (1998) On the genus Maccevethus Dallas (Heteroptera, Rhopalidae). Zoosystematica Rossica, 10, 84." type="journal article" year="1998">
Kerzhner 
<number id="783F24D8BD14FFE6249EFFA1FDD09A88" box="[483,546,942,966]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
